<HEADLINE> S. Leonean Rebel Leader Said to Be Under House </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Sierra Leoneang rebel leader
Foday Sanko has been put under house arrest in this Nigerian
city, a report here said today.
</P>
<P>
The news, however, could not be confirmed at this moment, as
neither the Nigerian Defense Headquarters nor the Sierra Leonean
High Commission here are available for comment at this moment.
</P>
<P>
The same report also quoted a senior member of Sanko's
Revolutionary United Front (RUF) as saying in a statement today
that the high command of RUF has declared with immediate effect
to sack Sanko as its leader for blocking the peace process.
</P>
<P>
However, the Nigerian Defense Headquarters on Tuesday denied
holding Sanko for anything incriminating while confirming the
presence of Sanko in Nigeria for a private visit.
</P>
<P>
The Defense Headquarters also dismissed reports that Sanko came
in with any ammunition as widely reported, adding that he was
free to enter into the country as a West African national.
</P>
<P>
"He's not in detention and he's not a threat to our security,"
a defense spokesman of the headquarters said. He noted that Sanko
is at the federal government guest house.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria has been in good relations with Sierra Leone. It was
only on last Friday that the two countries recently signed a
military agreement, under which Nigeria will help train Sierra
Leone's security agencies, including that country's Army, Navy,
Air Force and Police. 
</P>
</TEXT>
