<HEADLINE> Zairean Rebels Enter Kisangani to Meet Full </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 15 (Xinhua) -- The first group of victorious
rebels entered Zaire's strategic city of Kisangani this afternoon
and were received with full embrace by jubilant local inhabitants,
reported the Agence France-Presse (AFP).
</P>
<P>
When trucks transporting rebels circulated in the center of the
city by 14:00 GMT, there was no gunfire heard but only cries of
happiness and salutation from local inhabitants long expecting the
arrival of the soldiers of Laurent-Desire Kabila, AFP quoted a
witness -- who wished to remain anonymous -- as saying.
</P>
<P>
The Zairean government troops looted food warehouses and shops
of the city this morning and virtually gave no fight when they
fled, according to reports from Kisangani.
</P>
<P>
AFP quoted a spokesman of the rebels as saying in Goma today
that fighting was continuing in Kisangani and that the rebels have
taken the international airport, which is 17 kilometers from the
third biggest city of Zaire.
</P>
<P>
The French army evacuated about 15 Westerners, including French
diplomats, two journalists of AFP and several officials of
international humanitarian organizations, from Kisangani this
morning on a military aircraft to Central African Republic's
capital Bangui. 
