<HEADLINE> Zairean Rebels' Radio Announces Capture of Kisangani </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 15 (Xinhua) -- The radio of the Zairean rebels,
"Voice of People", announced this evening the capture of the
strategic city of Kisangani by its troops "after five hours of
cut-throat fighting".
</P>
<P>
The Agence France-Presse (AFP) quoted the radio as saying that
the fighting took place between "the Army of Liberation of the
Congo" and Zairean government troops, the FAZ, who were supported
by former Rwandan Hutu soldiers and Rwanda's extremist Hutu
"Interahamwes" militias.
</P>
<P>
It said that the Kisangani international airport was under the
control of the rebels since 11:00 (10:00 GMT) this morning.
</P>
<P>
It said that the local inhabitants have fled the city in fear
of "lootings and criminal acts" of the defeated government forces,
while the mercenaries hired by the Zairean government fled on
helicopters.
</P>
<P>
Kisangani is the third largest city of Zaire and capital of the
Upper Zaire region. Its fall has removed the last block to the
advance of the rebels east of the Zaire River.
</P>
<P>
The rebels have so far taken one fifth of the Zairean
territory. 
</P>
