<HEADLINE> Algerian Security Forces Surround Old City of Algiers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Algeria's security forces blocked
this afternoon all accessed to the old city of Algiers, Cashah,
where the militant group of Armed Islamic Group (GIA) is
reportedly active, according to reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
Police have blocked roads leading to Cashah, which is located
in the center of Algiers, while soldiers were patrolling the
outskirt of the town, but no gun fires were heard this afternoon,
said the reports.
</P>
<P>
Cashah, which has 1,700 inhabitants, is one of the strongholds
of the GIA which imposes its law on the local inhabitants and
whose members were seen walking around the narrow streets of the
town with weapons.
</P>
<P>
Several assassinations have recently taken place in Cashah and
the residents of other parts of Algiers dare not enter the area.
</P>
<P>
Three days ago, Algerian security forces killed 12 GIA members
in an anti-terrorist operation in another district of Algiers,
Beau Fraisier.
</P>
<P>
For more than one month, Algerian security forces have been
carrying out a large-scale operation against the GIA across the
country.
</P>
<P>
Algeria will hold its general elections on June 5 to put into
place a new two-chamber parliament. 
