<HEADLINE> Tanzania to Reduce International Telephone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 15 (Xinhua) -- The Tanzania
Telecommunications Company Limited (TTCL) has decided to reduce
its international telephone tariffs by up to 39.6 percent while
raise inland phone call charges by 25 percent from April 1.
</P>
<P>
TTCL Public Relations Manager Issa Sembawa said in a statement
issued here today that the new tariff is the continuation of the
implementation of the country's mission to achieve
tariff rebalance and harmonization.
</P>
<P>
He said the tariff structure is aimed at supporting the
country's economic development efforts by stimulating
international trade and tourism and attracting foreign investors
into Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
He said TTCL would also reduce the number of international
charge zones from five to three and retain two tariff structures
on cheap or discount rates.
</P>
<P>
There would be no changes for telex and telegraph services, he
added.
</P>
<P>
He said the international telephone tariff per minute for Zone
A will reduce from the current 2.5 U.S. Dollars to two Dollars and
inland telephone charges per minute will increase to about three
cents from about 2.6 cents. enditem

