<HEADLINE> Golden Cross Stolen from Church in Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 15 (Xinhua) -- A golden cross weighing five
kilograms was stolen from the Medhanialem Church in Lalibela of
Ethiopia, the Ethiopian News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The report said the golden cross, which is believed to have
existed for 800 years, was used only for ceremonial purposes.
</P>
<P>
The cross was stolen last Sunday night with only one of the
doors to the church broken into.
</P>
<P>
Local police said they believe that the mystery of the theft
revolves around those serving in the church, saying the theft
might be carried out by someone who knows the in and out of the
church.
</P>
<P>
The suspicion was reinforced by the fact that chalices,
jewelry and other crosses there were found intact.
</P>
<P>
The police have detained some 13 of the churchmen in
connection with the thievery, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
Lalibela Town is situated some 640 kilometers north of the
capital Addis Ababa. enditem

