on violences available so far.
</P>
<P>
The counting of ballots is now going on and the results are
expected to be coming out from tonight.
</P>
<P>
The elections were widely described as fair and peaceful,
according to official reports.
</P>
<P>
In Lagos, Nigeria's largest city and commercial center, the
situation was seen calmly and orderly.
</P>
<P>
As the government had imposed a traffic restriction, there
were few vehicles except those of patrolling police and election
officials during the polling period from 8:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics showed a total of some 56 million
Nigerians, slightly more than half of the its population, were
registered as voters.
</P>
<P>
It is not clear how many people have actually voted.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of the National Electoral Commission of Nigeria
Sumner Dagogo-Jack was quoted by reports from Aubja as
saying that the commission is impressed by the large turn-out of
the voters.
</P>
<P>
However, a Xinhua reporter gathered that only less than 300
people voted in the day at a polling station on the Victoria
Island in Lagos, where some 800 voters are registered. 
