<HEADLINE> World Record Holder Fails to Make Team for PanPac Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, March 16 (Xinhua) -- World 200 meters breaststroke
record holder Rebecca Brown failed to make the Australian squad
for the Pan Pacific Games in Adelaide, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Brown was beaten into fifth place over 200m by Samantha Riley
following her sixth place earlier in the 100m event.
</P>
<P>
Ian Thorpe, 14, became Australia's youngest representative,
replacing 1960 Rome Olympics 1500m gold medallist Jon Konrads.
</P>
<P>
