<HEADLINE> France: Turkey Has Right for EU Membership </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
APELDOORN, March 16 (Xinhua) -- France said today that the
European Union (EU) should make it clear to Ankara that Turkey has
the right for EU membership.
</P>
<P>
"Turkey has the right to join EU and that right has to be
confirmed forcefully," France's Foreign Minister Herve de Charette
told reporters at an informal EU foreign ministers meeting in the
Dutch town of Apeldoorn.
</P>
<P>
The French minister distanced his country sharply from a number
of EU countries whose leaders have ruled out Turkey's EU
membership.
</P>
<P>
De Charette said Turkey's accession to the EU was important for
the stability in the region, adding "We can only judge the
membership of a country on objective criteria, and certainly not
on religious or ethnic criteria."
</P>
<P>
He said France would like to include Turkey in a so-called
Permanent European Conference, a forum designed to get the EU
membership aspirants better prepared for the accession.
</P>
<P>
On March 4, a summit of the European People's Party made up of
parities from eight European countries, concluded in Brussels that
Turkey's EU membership was not acceptable at present.
</P>
<P>
Among the attendants of the summit were German Chancellor
Helmut Kohl, Spanish Prime Minister Jose-Maria Aznar and Italian
Prime Minister Romano Prodi. 
</P>
</TEXT>
