<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Today was the last day of a
match held in Shanghai, China's largest city, that tested the
intelligence of 200 teams composed of 1,400 middle and primary
school students from various parts of China.
</P>
<P>
Most of the students are from Shanghai and Suzhou City, in east
China's Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai OM Association will select two teams from the
winning contestants to attend the 18th World OM Contest, to be
held in the United States in June.
</P>
