<HEADLINE> Australian Neiwand Fails Doping Test </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Australian sprint cyclist Gary
Neiwand has tested positive to a banned stimulant, the Australian
Cycling Federation (ACF) said in Sydney on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The ACF said it had fined 30-year-old Neiwand 1,000 Australian
dollars (800 U.S. dollars) for testing positive to the banned
stimulant pseudoephedrine.
</P>
<P>
