<HEADLINE> Bridge Linking Shenzhen, Hong Kong Passes Experts Appraisal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, March 16 (Xinhua) -- A meeting in Snenzhen, in south
China's Guangdong Province, to discuss construction of a highway
bridge between this booming city and neighboring Hong kong ended
today.
</P>
<P>
Some 20 experts at the conference said that the significance of
another highway in the western part of Shenzhen would be in
maintaining the prosperity and stability of Hong Kong and for
developing the economy of the Pearl River Delta and the whole of
south China.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was organized by the China International
Engineering Consulting Corporation on behalf of China's State
Planning Commission.
</P>
<P>
After field studies in Shenzhen and Hong Kong were done and a
feasibility study completed, experts pointed out that the existing
three ports between the two cities can hardly meet development
demands.
</P>
<P>
According to the plan, a five-km-long highway bridge will be
built across the sea, linking Dongjiaotou in Shekou and Yuen Long
in Hong Kong. A 50-ha port area will also be built. Many Hong Kong
consortiums have showed an interest in the project, sources say.
</P>
</TEXT>
