<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Agro-Science Helps Northeast China Improve Harvests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Farmers in northeast China's
Heilongjiang Province attribute successively good harvests to
scientific farming methods that have now become standard in rural
areas.
</P>
<P>
The province is one of China's major grain producers and had a
record grain output of 30.465 billion kilograms in 1996, an
increase of 4.55 billion kilograms over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Ma Ting'ai, a young farmer in Fujin City, planted three ha of
rice and bred 50,000 fish in the paddy by closely following what
he had learned at a training class. His return amounted to 30,000
yuan.
</P>
<P>
At first, farmers didn't understand this when a pilot project
in farm standardization started in 10 counties in 1984. But
gradually more farmers like Ma helped popularize practices in
rural parts of the province in the late 1980s.
</P>
<P>
It took 34 years for the province to produce 15 billion
kilograms of grain after the founding of New China in 1949, but
only 13 more years to double that output, according to provincial
officials. Science and technology are said to have contributed 42
percent of that unprecedented growth.
</P>
<P>
The growing season in Yi'an County is only 120 to 125 days
long. Corn output per ha there was 1,995 kilograms in 1989. Then
agronomists introduced new rice strains and the use of plastic
sheeting while doubling the number of seedlings per hectare. By
1996 the county had a per ha corn output of 7,590 kg.
</P>
<P>
Agronomists are sent during the busy season to help ensure the
use of standardized farming methods. The province has held 25,000
training classes, benefitting more than two million farmers, and
adopted 810 scientific standards and helped supervise the whole
process of farming.
</P>
<P>
Standardized farming was used on 3.162 million ha in 1996,
accounting for 60.55 percent of the province's total crop area.
That coverage is expected to be expanded.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970316.0062 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-16 </DATE_TIME>
