conference to pay proper attention to the development of the
multi-ethnic and multi-religious communities in Nepal.
</P>
<P>
During the conference, some 100 anthropologists and
sociologists from Nepal, the United States, Japan, Australia and
Germany are expected to present and discuss 46 working papers on
topics including religious tradition, natural resources management
and ways of population control.  
