<HEADLINE> East Chinese Province Opening Wider to Outside World </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, March 16 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province has
plans to open wider to the outside world, with priority to be
given to the export-oriented economy and use of overseas
investment.
</P>
<P>
The province will give foreign trade licenses to a greater
number of enterprises, use agents for foreign trade, and help
build a number of profitable foreign trade firms into groups or
multinational enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Emphasis will also be placed on development zones and
foreign-funded enterprises, which are expected to give an impetus
to local economic growth.
</P>
<P>
The province intends to open two more counties and one or two
more ports to foreigners and to add group charter air routes for
tourists linking the provincial capital of Hefei and a local
scenic spot at Huangshan with foreign countries, such as Japan and
the Republic of Korea.
</P>
<P>
It also plans to participate in activities in other provinces
or abroad, including a TV Week in Europe, investment talks in Hong
Kong, and a commodity fair in the city of Xi'an in north China, in
a bid to make Anhui better known outside China and to increase
economic cooperation with other provinces and with foreign
countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
