</P>
<P>
The Washington Post:
</P>
<P>
-- Russian Foreign Minister Yevgeny Primakov began three days
of top-level meetings with U.S. officials on Saturday, in a
last-minute effort to resolve thorny arms control and security
issues that have cast a cloud of uncertainty over this week's
scheduled summit between U.S. President Bill Clinton and Russian
President Boris Yeltsin.
</P>
<P>
-- The United States joined other powers on Saturday in tacit
backing of Palestinian grievances against Israel, a quietly
dramatic sign of the Jewish state's growing diplomatic isolation.
</P>
