<HEADLINE> King Hussein Pays Condolence Visit To Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, March 16 (Xinhua) -- King Hussein of Jordan arrived
in Israel this afternoon for a nine-hour goodwill visit in the
wake of the bloody incident in which seven schoolgirls were shot
dead by a lone Jordanian soldier in Naharayim Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The monarch, who is accompanied by Prince Faisal and Princess
Aisha arrived at Ben Guriton Airport and received by Prime Minister
Binyamin Netanyahu.
</P>
<P>
The king went directly to Beit Shemish for condolence
visits to the bereaved families of the seven Israeli schoolgirls
despite the rain.
</P>
<P>
According to the schedule issued by the Government Press
Office Saturday night, the King then will proceed to
Hadassah-University Hospital in Jerusalem's Ein Kerem to visit a
girl pupil and a teacher wounded in the incident, and to
see President Ezer Weizman who underwent surgery in the same
hospital.
</P>
<P>
The king and Netanyahu are scheduled to hold talks this
evening, which will be followed by a joint press conference
in King David Hotel.
</P>
<P>
Hussein has so far declined to make an official visit to
Jerusalem. The last time he was in the city was for prime
minister Yitzhak Rabin's funeral in November 1995.
</P>
<P>
Observers here believe that Israel hopes to use the visit
to improve the strained relations with Jordan and soften
Jordan's position regarding Israel's decision to build a new
Jewish settlement at Har Homa in the Arab East Jerusalem.
</P>
</TEXT>
