<HEADLINE> All 88 on board C-130 Aircraft Confirmed Dead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, March 16 (Xinhua) -- All 88 passengers and crew
members of Iran's C-130 military plane that crashed over
Binaloud heights in northeastern Iran on Thursday are killed, an
official report said today.
</P>
<P>
Iran's official news agency IRNA reported that the announcement
was made by Iran's armed forces in a statement issued here
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that the reason for the crash about
700 km northeast of Tehran, is not known yet but a special
investigation team from the air force is probing into the
incident.
</P>
<P>
It added that as soon as any information become available
the nation will be informed.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that all passengers of the ill-fated plane
were either military personnel or their family members.
</P>
<P>
The last contact of the pilot with the control tower was
made at 18:06 hours local time (14:36 GMT) on Thursday. It
is assumed that the plane went down following its last contact
with the control tower.
</P>
<P>
The plane was en route from Dezful in southwestern Iran
to the religious city of Mashhad in the northeastern province
of Khorasan.
</P>
<P>
This was the second air mishap in 10 days in the
country. The last air crash occurred on March 3 as a
French-made Falcon aircraft crashed 25 km northeast of Ardebil
city in northeastern Iran. The Falcon pilot and three flight
engineers died in the Ardebil crash. 
</P>
</TEXT>
