<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Air Force Aircraft Crashes in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, March 16 (Xinhua) -- A Sri Lankan Air Force fighter
plane crashed Saturday night soon after taking off from the
military airfield at Hingurakgoda in Northern Province's capital
of Anuradhapura, according to police sources here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the aircraft had taken off on a mission
against Tamil rebels at Vakarai in Batticaloa District, Eastern
Province, last night and according to reports, was plying at an
altitude of around 10,000 feet (about 3,200 meters) when it burst
into flames.
</P>
<P>
The pilot, who was the only person aboard, ejected himself from
the plane and parachuted to the ground while the plane crashed
into the dried bed of a tank at Medigiriya in Polonnaruwa
District, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the crash is not yet known at present.
Investigations are proceeding, the sources added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
