<HEADLINE> Earthquake Rocks Central Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, March 16 (Xinhua) -- A strong earthquake measuring 5.6
on the Richter scale jolted central Japan this afternoon, but
there were no immediate reports of damage or injuries.
</P>
<P>
The quake, which struck at 2:51 p.m. (0551 GMT) and centered in
the eastern part of the central prefecture of Aichi, could be felt
as far away as Tokyo, 250 kilometers to the southwest, the
Meteorological Agency said.
</P>
<P>
Local police said they had no immediate reports of casualties
or property damage from the quake. 
</P>
