<HEADLINE> HK Hotel Gears Up Preparations for World Rugby Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's Hotel Furama has
geared up its preparations for accommodating some 250 players for
the coming World Cup Rugby Sevens just five days away -- and food
first.
</P>
<P>
To satisfy the mammoth appetite of the rugby players from
around the world is nothing easy, especially when a banana fetish
tops an already hefty menu.
</P>
<P>
The refrigerators and storerooms at the hotel are being stocked
up with a record amount of food in anticipation of the arrival
this week of 24 rugby teams for the three-day sporting event.
</P>
<P>
The players are expected to consume more in one meal than the
hotel usually serves to all its guests in one day, according to
the English-language newspaper Hong Kong Standard here today.
</P>
<P>
"The real challenge has been satisfying a demand for bananas,"
the report said.
</P>
<P>
For just one breakfast, food expected to be consumed include
120 kilograms of bananas, 90 loaves of toasting bread, 50 loaves
of measly bread, 35 kilograms of rice and 720 eggs, the newspaper
said.
</P>
<P>
And to go down with this, the players need 100 liters of fresh
orange juice, 60 liters of carrot juice and 80 liters of fruit
punch.
</P>
<P>
"While the order for just one meal is practically double the
amount of food and drink consumed by the entire hotel in a day,
we've ordered triple the number of bananas we've ever required in
a day before," said Elizabeth Iron, the hotel's public relations
and advertising manager.
</P>
<P>
But these guests had made no extra request for alcohol
consumption, Iron said.
</P>
<P>
"They don't drink. Well, until it's all over, of course.
They're professional players so drinking is a definite no-no," she
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
