government of Sheikh Hasina failed in all fronts during its
nine-month rule. "The country's sovereignty and democracy are at
stake and the nation has plunged into an abysmal situation due to
the misrule."
</P>
<P>
Referring to her arch-rival Hasina's call for cooperation,
Khaleda posed the question: "How can one cooperate with a
government which is selling out the country and making the lives
of people intolerable?"
</P>
<P>
She said Indian hegemony has been already established in
Bangladesh in the spheres of trade and commerce.
</P>
