<HEADLINE> Song Jian Leaves for Switzerland to Attend Forum Engelberg </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Chinese State Councillor and
Minister of State Science and Technology Commission Song Jian left
here today for Switzerland to attend and chair the Forum
Engelberg. which is scheduled to be held between March 18 and 21.
</P>
<P>
The subject of the conference will be "food and water -- an
issue concerning existence of human being." The subject is chosen
because the water and food are of great importance to the future
of earth, upon which the mankind live.
</P>
<P>
According to the organizers of the conference, the conference
has attracted many well-known scientists, economists, and
celebrated personage in various countries, including winners of
Nobel Prize for Physics Samuel C.C. Ting and Heinrich Rohrer; as
well as heads of International Rice Research Institute and
U.N. Food and Agriculture Organization.
</P>
<P>
Forum Engelberg, established in 1989, is an international forum
which gathers scientists, economists, and experts in policy-making
and culture field from various countries to discuss major
scientific research programs and other important issues of
contemporary science.
</P>
<P>
So far, the Forum Engelberg has held eight conferences and the
discussed topics have extended from pure science and technology to
a number of global issues in other fields. 
</P>
</TEXT>
