<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chang Edges Muster in Champions Cup Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Third seed Michael Chang edged
second seed Thomas Muster of Austria 6-1, 7-6 (7-1) at the
Champions Cup men's Tennis tournamentto in Indian Wells on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Chang will meet Bohdan Ulihrach of Czech Republic in the finals
to defend his Champions cup title.
</P>
<P>
Unseeded Ulihrach defeated Jonas Bjorkman of Sweden 6-3, 6-2 in
another semi-final match.
</P>
<P>
Ulihrach overwhelmed Pete Sampras of the United States in the
second round here.
</P>
<P>
Muster and Chang came into the match with identical
win-loss records this year of 15-2. Each had won one title in
four tournaments played this year. Each has won one Grand
Slam, the French Open.
</P>
<P>
Chang whipped Muster in the first set, taking service
breaks in the fourth and sixth games.
</P>
<P>
In the second set, Muster was unable to take the opportunity to
go ahead 5-3 in the second set on two break points in that eighth
game and lost the match later. 
</P>
</TEXT>
