<HEADLINE> Austrian Helicopter Crashes, killing four </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, March 15 (Xinhua) -- A helicopter crashed early today
in the forest at the northeast border of Lower Austria, killing
all the four people on board.
</P>
<P>
The Interior Ministry's AS N-355 helicopter took off from the
Wien-Schwechat airport near Vienna for a patrol mission but
crashed in the forest at 0:19 a.m., the Austrian Press Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
Ministry officials said the helicopter with a night vision
device controlled by a skilled pilot has served only for a
year. The cause of the crash is under investigation. 
</P>
