<BODY>
<HEADLINE> North Chinese Areas Making Joint Foreign Trade Effort </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, March 16 (Xinhua) -- The municipalities of
Beijing and Tianjin are making a concerted effort with Hebei
Province to form a tripartite export-oriented economy.
</P>
<P>
The three parties have been making a joint effort to establish
an economic center in north China, and the annual Tianjin Foreign
Trade Export Fair is a direct result of this cooperation. In the
past, the three formed an economic union for foreign trade via
Tianjin port. Then they decided to go their own ways but the
results were no better.
</P>
<P>
The three have now agreed to share foreign trade bureaus abroad
to open up world markets and make fuller use of Tianjin port, and
Hebei Province is ready to take steps to stabilize prices of farm
produce and by-products needed by the two cities for export.
</P>
<P>
Another example is the famous Tianjin Ya Pear and the Jingdong
Chinese Chestnut, which come mostly from Hebei, but the three have
equal export rights to them.
</P>
<P>
The Tianjin Bonded Zone and its favourable policies are wide
open to Beijing and Hebei for developing foreign trade, setting up
new projects, and bonded business.
</P>
<P>
The united efforts are bringing good results. Finished
industrial products account for 71.5 percent of the total exports
and the product mix has been improved considerably. Cooperation
has helped the sustained development of foreign exports. Hebei
alone had 3.47 billion US dollars in exports in 1996, a 13.5
percent increase, higher than the country's average. enditem
nnnn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
