<HEADLINE> Romania Ready to Join Satablization Forces for Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, March 15 (Xinhua) -- The Romanian government said
today that it is ready to join the proposed stablization forces
that will be sent to restore order in Albania.
</P>
<P>
The Romanian government expressed in a communique its deep
concern over the tense situation in Albania which it said is
likely to affect regional stability.
</P>
<P>
It called on all political groups in Albania to make concerted
efforts to ensure safety of the Albanian citizens and its national
stability.
</P>
<P>
The communique that Romania will cooperate with international
organizations in seeking effective ways to prevent the situation
there from going out of control.
</P>
<P>
The Romanian Foreign Ministry also expressed support for
efforts by international organizations, especially by the
Organization for Security and Cooperation (OSCE) and the European
Union (EU) in solving the Albanian crisis.
</P>
<P>
The Romanian news agency reported that eight Romanian students
and relatives of diplomats have been evacuated from Albania.
</P>
<P>
Zoe Petre, advisor of the Romanian president, said that
Romanian diplomats in Albania would not be evacuated because the
situation there would ease. 
</P>
</TEXT>
