<HEADLINE> Earthquake Jolts Bengkulu, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, March 16 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.12 on
the Richter scale struck Bengkulu Province, Indonesia, at 7:00
p.m. local time on Friday, the Antara News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Armin Paimin, a spokesman of the local meteorological and
geophysical office, said the epicenter was 187 kilometers
southwest of Bengkulu, the provincial capital.
</P>
<P>
The quake was felt by people in Bengkulu and its environs but
caused no casualty or material losses, he said.
</P>
<P>
Friday's tremor was the biggest the province has ever seen so
far this year.
</P>
<P>
The office has recorded a total of 50 tremors of varying
intensity in the province so far this year.
</P>
<P>
The province saw 418 quakes with an average intensity of 4.5 on
the Richter scale throughout 1996, he added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
