<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Park Marking Longitude-Latitude Intersection Under Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, March 16 (Xinhua) -- A science park marking the
intersection of 120 degrees east longitude and 30 degrees north
latitude is being built in Dayuan Town, east China's Zhejiang
Province.
</P>
<P>
According to geography experts, there are 12 total cross points
of longitude and latitude lines in China, 11 of which are located
in untraversed sea, forest or desert areas.
</P>
<P>
Only the spot at the foot of a mountain in Dayuan Town has
favorable transportation conditions.
</P>
<P>
A tower will be built in the park at the exact point of
intersection. At noon, sunlight will be able to shine through the
passage. In addition, miniature replicas of some symbolic
geographical wonders around the world will be constructed.
</P>
<P>
Total cost of the park stands at 20 million yuan (2.4 million
US dollars),
</P>
<P>
Experts say 120 degree east longitude is the standard line of
Beijing Time. When the sun shines on the line at noon, most places
along the line report 12:00 Beijing Time. However, Beijing proper
has to wait another 16 minutes for noon to arrive.
</P>
<P>
The 30 degree north latitude line has some famous connections,
cutting through five well-known areas, including the Bermuda
Islands, the heaven for dinosaurs 200 million years ago, the
birthplaces of the world's three major religions, and places which
have undergone extensive crust activities.
</P>
<P>
Also along the line are world-famous tides, and Egyptian
pyramids and sphinx.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
