<HEADLINE> Environmental Awareness Emphasized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 16 (Xinhua) -- It's essential that the public be
aware about environmental issues, stressed Wang Zhibao, Chinese
Vice-Minister of Forestry, during a recent interview with the
Xinhua News Agency.
</P>
<P>
The official said that significant improvements will only be
achieved when the whole society understands the importance of
conservation efforts and actively participates.
</P>
<P>
"Conservation awareness should start in primary schooling,"
Wang said, "we will make efforts to cooperate with other
authorities to enhance the education program."
</P>
<P>
"Even though consciousness about environmental concerns has
been raised, the understanding that to protect nature is to
protect the future of humanity has not been explained to many
people," the Vice-Minister said.
</P>
<P>
Wang noted that the fact that journalists and teachers tend to
be more aware of the importance of protecting natural resources
will help China realize wider understanding of ecological concerns
at all levels of society.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that in China a total of 10 million people have
been involved in such activities as "love-birds week" and
"wildlife protection week".
</P>
<P>
And the first popular science and education base for wildlife
protection, established by the Beijing Breeding Center for
Endangered Animals two years ago, has received 40,000 local
teenagers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
