<HEADLINE> More Air Routes for Huangshan Mountain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Huangshan Airport, in east China's
Anhui Province, will open two new air routes by March 30 -- one to
Qingdao, a coastal city in east China's Shandong Province, and
another to Yichang City in central China's Hubei Province.
</P>
<P>
With the new routes, Huangshan will provide 70 total flights
and handle about 12,000 passengers each week, a 15 percent rise
over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the airport will increase its flights this year to
major tourist cities, including Beijing, Shanghai, Guangzhou,
Xi'an, and Wuhan. There are presently 14 flights from Huangshan to
Guangzhou per week.
</P>
<P>
Huangshan Mountain is one of China's tourist meccas, famous for
its pines and uniquely-shaped stones.  
</P>
</TEXT>
