<HEADLINE> China Builds Button Town in Zhejiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, March 16 (Xinhua) -- China will build a "Button Town"
in the world's largest button market of Qiaotou, a town in east
China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
Qiaotou is home of 3,100 button stands. In 1996, more than 15
billion buttons were sold there -- nearly three for each person on
earth -- and accounting for 85 percent of China's button demand.
</P>
<P>
Qiaotou is also the largest button production base in China,
with the output accounting for about 70 percent of the country's
total.
</P>
<P>
Button Town involves a 75 million yuan investment.
</P>
<P>
A button salesroom was built in Qiaotou in the mid-1980s, with
a floor space of 80,000 square meters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
