<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Shuttlers Take Four of Five Titles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 15 (Xinhua/OANA) -- China dominated the
All-England badminton tournament in Brimingham, winning four of
the five finals Saturday to put itself as an odds-on favorite in
the upcoming world championships in Scotland.
</P>
<P>
In the men's singles, China's Dong Jiong defeated fellow
countryman Sun Jun 15-9, 15-5 in the final. In women's singles,
China's Ye Zhaoying also downed another Chinese, Gong Zhichao,
11-1, 11-3 in just 19 minutes.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese also won in the women's doubles where the pair of
Olympic champions Ge Fei and Gu Jun beat the Indonesian duo of
Eliza and Resiana Zelin 15-6, 15-9.
</P>
<P>
Ge came back in mixed doubles, teaming with Liu Yong to rout
Trikus Heryanto and Minarti Timur of Indonesia 15-10, 15-2.
</P>
<P>
The only non-Chinese triumph came in men's doubles, where the
South Korean team of Ha Tae-Kwon and Kang Kyung-Jin beat the
Danish pair of Jon Holst-Christensen and Michael Sogaard 15-11,
17-16.
</P>
<P>
The world championships will be held in Glasgow from May 25 to
June 1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
