<HEADLINE> Chinese Capital Fruitful in Labor Export in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 16 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese capital city chalked
up substantial achievements in labor exports in 1996, signing
contracts worth 880 million US dollars and realizing 450 million
US dollars in business, and sending 4,500 workers abroad.
</P>
<P>
The information was released by Sun Anming, Vice-Director of
the Municipal Foreign Economic and Trade Commission of Beijing,
who spoke at a recent work conference of the city on the issue.
</P>
<P>
According to Sun, the Beijing Urban Construction Corporation
won the bid for a subway project in Tehran, which has a
contractual value of 153 million US dollars and now ranks as the
largest labor contract for a local firm in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Also last year, the Beijing International Economic Cooperation
clinched a deal for an irrigation project in Pakistan worth 26.7
million US dollars. Meanwhile, the Beijing Residential House
Construction Corporation sealed a labor export contract in
Singapore and signed two more contracts valued at 51.13 million US
dollars.
</P>
<P>
In addition to consolidating the older markets in Southeast
Asia and West Asia, local labor exporters have opened some new
markets, including those in Israel and Sri Lanka, Sun said.
</P>
<P>
According to Yi Xiqun, director of the commission who also
spoke at the meeting, the city government last year took steps to
coordinate all concerned departments and industries so as to bring
the city's advantages in technology, personnel, funds, designing
and engineering into full play.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, Sun noted, the city plans to sign labor export
contracts worth one billion US dollars, realize 500 million US
dollars in business and export 4,500 workers.
</P>
<P>
This year, the city government will organize 11 local labor
exporters to participate in two fairs involving Beijing's
international economic and technological cooperation, to be held
in Singapore and Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, more local companies will be granted rights to
export labors and undertake imports and exports, he said.
</P>
<P>
According to the director, Beijing leads the country in labor
exports. 
</P>
</TEXT>
