<HEADLINE> Damm, Johansson to Vie for Copenhagen Tennis Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Heavy hitting Martin Damm
overwhelmed Slovakian Karol Kucera 6-4, 3-6, 6-3 on Saturday to
reach the final of the Copenhagen Open tennis tournament.
</P>
<P>
The second-seeded Czech in Sunday's final will face
fifth-seeded Thomas Johansson of Sweden, who easily beat German
Lars Burgsmuller in their semi-final 6-2, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Damm, who has relied on his strong and accurate serve
throughout the tournament, got in 65 percent of his first serves
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
In doubles, Russia's Andrei Olhovskiy and New Zealand's Brett
Steven pulled off a major upset by beating top-seeded Menno
Oosting of the Netherlands and Libor Pimek of Belgium 7-6 (7-6),
6-2.
</P>
<P>
The will face Danish pair Kenneth Carlsen and Frederik
Fetterlein, who also score an upset over Frenchmen Guillaume Raoux
and Fabrice Santoro, 7-5, 6-4. 
